---
layout: base.njk
title: Capydocs Themes
description: Static gallery ready for Cloudflare Pages to list every custom theme from this repository.
---
<style>
  .overview {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    color: #cdd0d6;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .theme-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
  }

  .theme-card {
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
    border-radius: 1rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
    background: rgba(21, 23, 31, 0.85);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .theme-eyebrow {
    text-transform: uppercase;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: #ffb4c8;
  }

  .theme-card h2 {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .theme-meta {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: #b5b9c3;
  }

  .theme-meta span {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
    border-radius: 999px;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.8rem;
  }

  .theme-links {
    margin-top: auto;
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .theme-links a {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.35rem;
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 600;
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);
  }
</style>

<section class="overview">
  <p>
    Each folder inside <code>/themes</code> ships a <code>theme.json</code> manifest that Capydocs can ingest to register
    a custom theme. Eleventy scans those folders to build both this gallery and the machine-friendly endpoint
    <code><a href="/themes.json">/themes.json</a></code>, perfect for deployment automation.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="theme-grid">
  {% for theme in themes %}
    <article class="theme-card">
      <span class="theme-eyebrow">{{ theme.base | upper }} base</span>
      <h2>{{ theme.name }}</h2>
      <p>{{ theme.description or "No description" }}</p>
      <div class="theme-meta">
        <span>ID: <code>{{ theme.id }}</code></span>
        <span>Assets: <code>{{ theme.assetsUrl }}</code></span>
      </div>
      <div class="theme-links">
        <a href="{{ theme.cssUrl }}">CSS</a>
        <a href="{{ theme.assetsUrl }}/theme.json">Manifest</a>
        <a href="{{ theme.zipUrl }}" download>ZIP</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  {% endfor %}
</section>
